#: ../../library/site.rst:2
msgid ":mod:`!site` --- Site-specific configuration hook"
msgstr ":mod:`!site` --- Gancho de configuraĂ§ĂŁo especĂ­fico do site"

#: ../../library/site.rst:7
msgid "**Source code:** :source:`Lib/site.py`"
msgstr "**CĂłdigo-fonte:** :source:`Lib/site.py`"

#: ../../library/site.rst:13
msgid ""
"**This module is automatically imported during initialization.** The "
"automatic import can be suppressed using the interpreter's :option:`-S` "
"option."
msgstr ""
"**Este mĂłdulo Ă© importado automaticamente durante a inicializaĂ§ĂŁo.** A "
"importaĂ§ĂŁo automĂˇtica pode ser suprimida usando a opĂ§ĂŁo :option:`-S` do "
"interpretador."

#: ../../library/site.rst:18
msgid ""
"Importing this module normally appends site-specific paths to the module "
"search path and adds :ref:`callables <site-consts>`, including :func:`help` "
"to the built-in namespace. However, Python startup option :option:`-S` "
"blocks this and this module can be safely imported with no automatic "
"modifications to the module search path or additions to the builtins.  To "
"explicitly trigger the usual site-specific additions, call the :func:`main` "
"function."
msgstr ""
"A importaĂ§ĂŁo deste mĂłdulo normalmente anexa caminhos especĂ­ficos do site ao "
"caminho de pesquisa de mĂłdulos e adiciona :ref:`chamĂˇveis <site-consts>`, "
"incluindo :func:`help` ao espaĂ§o de nomes embutido. No entanto, a opĂ§ĂŁo de "
"inicializaĂ§ĂŁo do Python :option:`-S` bloqueia isso e este mĂłdulo pode ser "
"importado com seguranĂ§a sem modificaĂ§Ăµes automĂˇticas no caminho de pesquisa "
"de mĂłdulos ou adiĂ§Ăµes aos mĂłdulos embutidos. Para acionar explicitamente as "
"adiĂ§Ăµes usuais especĂ­ficas do site, chame a funĂ§ĂŁo :func:`main`."

#: ../../library/site.rst:25
msgid ""
"Importing the module used to trigger paths manipulation even when using :"
"option:`-S`."
msgstr ""
"A importaĂ§ĂŁo do mĂłdulo usado para acionar a manipulaĂ§ĂŁo de caminhos, mesmo "
"ao usar :option:`-S`."

#: ../../library/site.rst:32
msgid ""
"It starts by constructing up to four directories from a head and a tail "
"part. For the head part, it uses ``sys.prefix`` and ``sys.exec_prefix``; "
"empty heads are skipped.  For the tail part, it uses the empty string and "
"then :file:`lib/site-packages` (on Windows) or :file:`lib/python{X.Y[t]}/"
"site-packages` (on Unix and macOS). (The optional suffix \"t\" indicates "
"the :term:`free-threaded build`, and is appended if ``\"t\"`` is present in "
"the :data:`sys.abiflags` constant.) For each of the distinct head-tail "
"combinations, it sees if it refers to an existing directory, and if so, adds "
"it to ``sys.path`` and also inspects the newly added path for configuration "
"files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../library/site.rst:44
msgid "Support for the \"site-python\" directory has been removed."
msgstr "Suporte para o diretĂłrio \"site-python\" foi removido."

#: ../../library/site.rst:47
msgid ""
"On Unix, :term:`Free threading <free threading>` Python installations are "
"identified by the \"t\" suffix in the version-specific directory name, such "
"as :file:`lib/python3.13t/`."
msgstr ""
"No Unix, as instalaĂ§Ăµes do Python :term:`threads livres <free threading>` "
"sĂŁo identificadas pelo sufixo \"t\" no nome do diretĂłrio especĂ­fico da "
"versĂŁo, como :file:`lib/python3.13t/`."

#: ../../library/site.rst:54
msgid ""
":mod:`!site` is no longer responsible for updating :data:`sys.prefix` and :"
"data:`sys.exec_prefix` on :ref:`sys-path-init-virtual-environments`. This is "
"now done during the :ref:`path initialization <sys-path-init>`. As a result, "
"under :ref:`sys-path-init-virtual-environments`, :data:`sys.prefix` and :"
"data:`sys.exec_prefix` no longer depend on the :mod:`!site` initialization, "
"and are therefore unaffected by :option:`-S`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../library/site.rst:63
msgid ""
"When running under a :ref:`virtual environment <sys-path-init-virtual-"
"environments>`, the ``pyvenv.cfg`` file in :data:`sys.prefix` is checked for "
"site-specific configurations. If the ``include-system-site-packages`` key "
"exists and is set to ``true`` (case-insensitive), the system-level prefixes "
"will be searched for site-packages, otherwise they won't."
msgstr ""
"Ao executar em um :ref:`ambiente virtual <sys-path-init-virtual-"
"environments>`, o arquivo ``pyvenv.cfg`` em :data:`sys.prefix` Ă© verificado "
"em busca de configuraĂ§Ăµes especĂ­ficas do site. Se a chave ``include-system-"
"site-packages`` existir e estiver definida como ``true`` (sem distinĂ§ĂŁo "
"entre maiĂşsculas e minĂşsculas), os prefixos de nĂ­vel de sistema serĂŁo "
"pesquisados em busca de site-packages; caso contrĂˇrio, nĂŁo serĂŁo."

#: ../../library/site.rst:73
msgid ""
"A path configuration file is a file whose name has the form :file:`{name}."
"pth` and exists in one of the four directories mentioned above; its contents "
"are additional items (one per line) to be added to ``sys.path``.  Non-"
"existing items are never added to ``sys.path``, and no check is made that "
"the item refers to a directory rather than a file.  No item is added to "
"``sys.path`` more than once.  Blank lines and lines beginning with ``#`` are "
"skipped.  Lines starting with ``import`` (followed by space or tab) are "
"executed."
msgstr ""
"Um arquivo de configuraĂ§ĂŁo de caminho Ă© aquele cujo nome tem o formato :file:"
"`{name}.pth` e que existe em um dos quatro diretĂłrios mencionados acima; seu "
"conteĂşdo sĂŁo itens adicionais (um por linha) a serem adicionados ao ``sys."
"path``. Itens inexistentes nunca sĂŁo adicionados ao ``sys.path`` e nĂŁo Ă© "
"verificado se o item se refere a um diretĂłrio, e nĂŁo a um arquivo. Nenhum "
"item Ă© adicionado ao ``sys.path`` mais de uma vez. Linhas em branco e linhas "
"iniciadas com ``#`` sĂŁo ignoradas. Linhas iniciadas com ``import`` (seguidas "
"de espaĂ§o ou tabulaĂ§ĂŁo) sĂŁo executadas."

#: ../../library/site.rst:83
msgid ""
"An executable line in a :file:`.pth` file is run at every Python startup, "
"regardless of whether a particular module is actually going to be used. Its "
"impact should thus be kept to a minimum. The primary intended purpose of "
"executable lines is to make the corresponding module(s) importable (load 3rd-"
"party import hooks, adjust :envvar:`PATH` etc). Any other initialization is "
"supposed to be done upon a module's actual import, if and when it happens. "
"Limiting a code chunk to a single line is a deliberate measure to discourage "
"putting anything more complex here."
msgstr ""
"Uma linha executĂˇvel em um arquivo :file:`.pth` Ă© executada a cada "
"inicializaĂ§ĂŁo do Python, independentemente de um mĂłdulo em particular ser "
"realmente usado. Seu impacto deve, portanto, ser reduzido ao mĂ­nimo. O "
"objetivo principal das linhas executĂˇveis Ă© tornar o(s) mĂłdulo(s) "
"correspondente(s) importĂˇvel (carregar ganchos de importaĂ§ĂŁo de terceiros, "
"ajustar :envvar:`PATH` etc). Qualquer outra inicializaĂ§ĂŁo deve ser feita na "
"importaĂ§ĂŁo real de um mĂłdulo, se e quando isso acontecer. Limitar um "
"fragmento de cĂłdigo a uma Ăşnica linha Ă© uma medida deliberada para "
"desencorajar colocar qualquer coisa mais complexa aqui."

#: ../../library/site.rst:94
msgid ""
"The :file:`.pth` files are now decoded by UTF-8 at first and then by the :"
"term:`locale encoding` if it fails."
msgstr ""
"Os arquivos :file:`.pth` agora sĂŁo decodificados primeiro por UTF-8 e depois "
"pela :term:`codificaĂ§ĂŁo da localidade` se falhar."

#: ../../library/site.rst:102
msgid ""
"For example, suppose ``sys.prefix`` and ``sys.exec_prefix`` are set to :file:"
"`/usr/local`.  The Python X.Y library is then installed in :file:`/usr/local/"
"lib/python{X.Y}`.  Suppose this has a subdirectory :file:`/usr/local/lib/"
"python{X.Y}/site-packages` with three subsubdirectories, :file:`foo`, :file:"
"`bar` and :file:`spam`, and two path configuration files, :file:`foo.pth` "
"and :file:`bar.pth`.  Assume :file:`foo.pth` contains the following::"
msgstr ""
"Por exemplo, suponha que ``sys.prefix`` e ``sys.exec_prefix`` sejam "
"definidos com :file:`/usr/local`. A biblioteca Python X.Y Ă© instalado em :"
"file:`/usr/local/lib/python{X.Y}`. Suponha que isso tenha um subdiretĂłrio :"
"file:`/usr/local/lib/python{X.Y}/site-packages` com trĂŞs subsubdiretĂłrios, :"
"file:`foo`, :file:`bar` e :file:`spam`, e dois caminhos arquivos de "
"configuraĂ§ĂŁo, :file:`foo.pth` e :file:`bar.pth`.  Presuma que :file:`foo."
"pth` contĂ©m o seguinte::"

#: ../../library/site.rst:110
msgid ""
"# foo package configuration\n"
"\n"
"foo\n"
"bar\n"
"bletch"
msgstr ""
"# configuraĂ§ĂŁo do pacote foo\n"
"\n"
"foo\n"
"bar\n"
"bletch"

#: ../../library/site.rst:116
msgid "and :file:`bar.pth` contains::"
msgstr "e que :file:`bar.pth` contĂ©m::"

#: ../../library/site.rst:118
msgid ""
"# bar package configuration\n"
"\n"
"bar"
msgstr ""
"# configuraĂ§ĂŁo do pacote bar\n"
"\n"
"bar"

#: ../../library/site.rst:122
msgid ""
"Then the following version-specific directories are added to ``sys.path``, "
"in this order::"
msgstr ""
"Em seguida, os seguintes diretĂłrios especĂ­ficos da versĂŁo sĂŁo adicionados a "
"``sys.path``, nesta ordem::"

#: ../../library/site.rst:125
msgid ""
"/usr/local/lib/pythonX.Y/site-packages/bar\n"
"/usr/local/lib/pythonX.Y/site-packages/foo"
msgstr ""
"/usr/local/lib/pythonX.Y/site-packages/bar\n"
"/usr/local/lib/pythonX.Y/site-packages/foo"

#: ../../library/site.rst:128
msgid ""
"Note that :file:`bletch` is omitted because it doesn't exist; the :file:"
"`bar` directory precedes the :file:`foo` directory because :file:`bar.pth` "
"comes alphabetically before :file:`foo.pth`; and :file:`spam` is omitted "
